        <num>CC 2355.1</num>
        <heading>2355.1.  Judicial authorization to manage the community</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2355.1.  Judicial authorization to manage the community
When a spouse is an absent person, the other spouse, upon showing that such action is in the best interest of the family, may be authorized by the court in a summary proceeding to manage, alienate, encumber, or lease community property that the absent spouse has the exclusive right to manage, alienate, encumber, or lease.</p>
        </content>
